      <description>&lt;p&gt;For my final project for an observational astronomy class at Guilford College, I used a method called Lucky Imaging to photograph planets and incorporate them into artistic photographs. The project was exhibited as a &lt;a href=&#34;poster.pdf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;poster presentation&lt;/a&gt; at the Guilford Undergraduate Symposium, and turned into an 
&lt;a href=&#34;/hollisakins.github.io/~akinshol/publication/astro&#34;&gt;article&lt;/a&gt; which was published in the October 2018 edition of The Physics Teacher.&lt;/p&gt;
